# Delegation And Capture

- When spawning subagents, pass a compact packet: goal, constraints, files, recalled memory, and acceptance checks.
- Do not delegate with only the raw user prompt when durable memory is relevant.
- Save clear repo-wide technical choices with `tools/agent/capture.sh`.
- Save user-specific workflow preferences and active task state to local memory, not shared memory.
- When durability is unclear, ask before writing memory.
- Before wrapping up, run `tools/agent/closeout.sh` and capture any missing durable choices.
